'''Taishōjin''' (太歳神, たいさいしん) is one of the {{ill|Eight Guardian Deities|ja|八将神|1=Eight Directional Deities|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Guardian Deities|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Directional Deities|qq=}} in [[:en:Onmyōdō|Onmyōdō]]. In some calendars, it is written as '''Daisai''' or '''Taisai''' (太さい). Taishōjin is also considered the husband of {{ill|Taiyinjin|ja|太陰神|1=Taionjin|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taiyinjin|13=User:Immanuelle/Taionjin|qq=}}, another member of the Eight Guardian Deities. In [[:en:Buddhism|Buddhism]], the {{ill|honji|ja|本地|1=Honji suijaku|2=ja|3=本地垂迹|lt=Honji|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/honji|qq=}} (spiritual essence) of Taishōjin is identified as [[:en:Bhaisajyaguru|Yakushi Nyorai Medicine Buddha]].

Taishōjin is regarded as the essence of [[:en:Jupiter|Jupiter]] (Suihoshi, the Star of the Year) and is believed to govern the generation of all things throughout the {{ill|Four Seasons|ja|四季|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Four Seasons|qq=}}. As a monarch-like deity, Taishōjin exerts influence over all directions. Due to its association with Jupiter, Taishōjin embodies characteristics related to {{ill|trees|ja|樹木|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/trees|qq=}} and plants. Activities such as planting trees or vegetation in the direction where Taishōjin resides are considered auspicious, while cutting trees or mowing grass in this direction is regarded as inauspicious.

As a sovereign deity, disputes such as [[:en:Legal proceeding|lawsuits]] or negotiations, as well as funerals and demolitions, are thought to invite misfortune. However, activities such as [[:en:Saving|savings]], [[:en:Architecture|construction]] of houses, renovations, relocations, {{ill|business transactions|ja|商取引|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/business transactions|qq=}}, [[:en:Marriage|marriage]], or employment are considered highly auspicious when performed in Taishōjin’s direction.

The direction of Taishōjin corresponds to the position of the [[:en:Earthly Branches|Chinese zodiac]] for the respective year.
